==English==
===Suffix===
'''-eth'''

# {{archaic}} Used to form the [[third-person]] [[singular]] [[present tense]] of verbs.
#:''goeth'', ''maketh''

====Usage note====
*This suffix is sometimes used to make mock, [[nonce]] verbs in any person, number or tense, but these are strictly incorrect.
*:As Shakespeare might have said, ''"Why don't you goeth boileth your head?";'' the correct form would be (presuming that he was suggesting this course of action to only one person), ''"Why dost thou not go boil thy head?"''
